messages.message:
I get a rate limiter exception from openai in model service logs when uploading documents in AIHub. Has anyone else seen this?

```openai.RateLimitError: Error code: 429 - {'error': {'message': 'You exceeded your current quota, please check your plan and billing details. For more information on this error, read the docs: https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/error-codes/api-errors.', 'type': 'insufficient_quota', 'param': None, 'code': 'insufficient_quota'}}```

This is what's in `env-local-overrides` when starting all services. (removing the power user aws keys doesn't change the result):

```{
    "audit_logs_export_endpoint": "RABBIT_MQ",
    "base": {
        "audit_logs_export_endpoint": "RABBIT_MQ",
        "AIHUB_UDF_EXECUTION": "LOCAL",
        "ENABLE_LAMBDA": false,
        "IS_ST_AIHUB": true,
        "aws_access_key_id": "[REDACTED]",
        "aws_secret_access_key": "[REDACTED]",
        "aws_session_token": "[REDACTED]",
        "namespace": "insan-use2-local-testing-instabase",
        "aws_default_region": "us-east-1"
    }
}```
Even after removing the keys, I still get the same issue
can you confirm that your `env-local-secrets` matches what's in 1password?
specifically compare the values for openai_api_key
yeah the openai_api_key matches

I don't know that you can. It just shows you the usage tier for the whole account. I'm also not seeing what user that key is associated with, because it appears to be a legacy key. FWIW you should be getting rate limit info returned as a header (https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/rate-limits#rate-limits-in-headers) in the response

maybe we're running into rate limit issues because more people are using this key with Cursor and are indexing our codebase?
